IT was little expected by the Colledge of Physicians, that after (
   〈…〉
) they had openly declared in their Publick Assembly, that none of them would oppose the Apothecaries Bill, and some perhaps beyond their Duty had actually assisted them therein, they should for all that find themselves frequently reflected upon both in their Publick Papers and Pleadings to the Two Houses of Parliament, which occasions this Short but Necessary Vindication of the Colledge and Faculty.
